<body> 
<center>
<h2>THE NATIONAL COMMISSION ON ECONOMIC GROWTH AND TAX REFORM</h2></center><p> 
<hr>
<p> 
<p> 
<p> 
<p> 
<p> 
<center><b>PUBLIC HEARING ON TAX REFORM</b></center>  
<center>HELD ON CAPITOL HILL</center>  
<center>Wednesday, June 28, 1995</center> 
<p> 
<p> 
<p>  
<p> 
<p>
<p>
<center><b>The National Commission on Economic Growth and Tax Reform</center> 
<center>1133 Connecticut Avenue, N.W., Suite 1010</center> 
<center>Washington, D.C.  20036</center>
<center>(202) 775-2375</b></center> 
<p> 
<hr>
<p>
<center><a name="CONTENTS"><h4>CONTENTS</h4></a></center> 
<p> 
<p>
<ul>
<li><a href="#COMMISSION MEMBERS IN ATTENDANCE"> COMMISSION MEMBERS IN ATTENDANCE:</a><br>
<li><a href="#COMMISSION MEMBERS NOT ATTENDING">COMMISSION MEMBERS NOT ATTENDING:</a><br>
<li><a href="#PARTICIPATING CONGRESSMEN AND SENATORS">PARTICIPATING CONGRESSMEN AND SENATORS:</a><br>
<li><a href="#Chairman Kemp">Jack Kemp</a>, Opening Remarks<br>     
<li><a href="#Bill Archer">Congressman Bill Archer</a>, Chairman House Ways and Means Committee<br>
<li><a href="#Senator Sam Nunn">Senator Sam Nunn</a><br>     
<li><a href="#Pete V. Domenici">Senator Pete V. Domenici<br>     
<li><a href="#Richard K. Armey">Congressman Richard K. Armey</a>  <a href="#Richard K. Armey">etc...</a>, House Majority Leader<br>      
<li><a href="#Connie Mack">Senator Connie Mack</a>,  Chairman, Joint Economic Committee  
</ul>
<p>
<p>
<hr>
<p>
<p>
<p>
<p>
<center>
<h4><a name="COMMISSION MEMBERS IN ATTENDANCE">COMMISSION MEMBERS IN ATTENDANCE:</a></h4></center>
<p> 
<p> 
<dd><b>JACK KEMP:</b> Co-Director Empower America</dd> 
<p>
<dd><b>J. KENNETH BLACKWELL:</dd></b> Ohio State Treasurer
