		<b>CHAIRMAN KEMP:</b>  Frank Hayes.<p>

		<b>MR. HAYES:</b>  Yes.  Herman, I think, just to echo
what Mr. Renner said, it has to be understandable.  <p>

		And that's why I like the flat tax, because if
the average individual does not understand it -- and
right now nobody, pretty much, understands the Tax Code
unless you work with it every single day -- if you
don't get that understanding on the part of the average
individual, if you do not reach that as part of your
recommendations, then you won't, in my estimation, have
the groundswell of support, because people won't know
what they're for.  <p>

		So, it has to be something that is simple
enough that it's understandable to the average person.  <p>

