<H3>Stan Evans to Explore the Religious Roots of Freedom</H3>
<P>
Young America's Foundation is pleased to announce a new lecture series for the 1996-97 academic year.
<table align=right width="320" hspace="5">
<tr><td><B><I>M. Stanton Evans</B>, author of </I>The Theme is 
Freedom<I>, will tour the country on behalf of 
Young America's Found-ation, lecturing on the role 
religion played in shaping the United States and its 
tradition of freedom.</td><td>
<IMG SRC="stan2.gif" ALT="M. Stanton Evans" WIDTH=100>
</td>
</tr>
</table>
This series will feature author and journalist <B>M. Stanton 
Evans</B>, who will discuss America's religious 
heritage and the role of religion in establishing our tradition of 
freedom.
<P>
If you would like to bring Mr. Evans to your campus to 
discuss this important issue, call <B>Patrick Coyle 
</B>at 1-800-292-9231.
