<BR>
<H3>Senator Wallop Joins Speaker Program</H3><BR>
Former United States Senator 
    <B>Malcolm Wallop </B>is now 
     available to defend freedom and liberty on your campus 
through the Foundation's speaker program. As a three-term Senator from 
Wyoming, Malcolm Wallop was a leader on various issues such 
asthe flat tax, federal deregulation, private property rights, and a 
strong national defense.
<table align=left width="200" hspace="5">
<tr><td><IMG SRC="wallop.gif" ALT="Former US Senator Malcom Wallop"><BR>
<I>Former Wyoming Senator <B>Malcolm Wallop </B>has been a longtime defender 
of private property rights.</I><BR>
</td></tr>
</table> 
<P>Having served on numerous congressional committees, 
Senator Wallop is an expert on many issues. He was the first to 
propose a space-based defense system in 1976. His efforts in 1981 led 
to cuts in inheritance and gift taxes. He is also knowledgeable on 
environmental issues. His latest effort has been to lead the fight 
against the Clinton Administration's &quot;War on the West.&quot;  Senator Wallop 
was successful in stopping the government's assault on 
Western mining, grazing, and water rights, seeing the government's efforts 
as an attempt to limit the rights of individuals and the states. 
<P>
Senator Wallop has written for a number of distinguished 
publications, such as <I>National Review, </I>the<I> Economist, U.S. News 
and World Report,</I> the <I>American 
Spectator</I>, the <I>Wall Street Journal</I>,  
and the <I>New York Times</I>. The Senator has appeared on many 
television programs such as <I>Nightline, </I>the 
<I>Today Show, CBS Morning News</I>, and the <I>McNeil-Lehrer News Hour.</I>
<P>Currently, he is Chairman of Frontiers of Freedom, a 
non-profit organization dedicated to the promotion of personal freedom 
and the reduction of federal fiscal and regulatory powers. He 
recently advocated reforming the Endangered Species Act and 
privatizing Social Security.  Senator Wallop continues to be a Wyoming 
rancher and businessman. 
<P>
<BR>If you are interested in bringing Senator 
Wallop to your school, please call <B>Patrick Coyle 
</B>at 1-800-292-9231.<BR>
<P>
<HR>
<a name="contact">
<P>
<BR>
<a href="#contents">Table of Contents</a>
