<p>

<p>
<hr>
<center>
<a name="phil"><h3>Philadelphia Society:<br>
Rub Elbows with Conservative Academics</h3></a>[ <a href="#contents">Contents </a>]
</center>
<p>
The Philadelphia Society will hold its 31st Annual Nationai Meeting April 28 to April 30 at the Sheraton Society Hill in Philadelphia. This year's topic is "Thinking the Unthinkable: The Successful Challenge to the Welfare State." Students interested in attending or receiving more information may write The Philadelphia Society, 109 West Main Street, North Adams, Michigan 49262, or call (517) 287-4266. 
Young America' s Foundation will host a dinner on Saturday, April 29, as part of the Philadelphia Society's meeting. The dinner is free to students, but seating is limited. If you are interested in attending, please call Marc Short at the Foundation: 1-800-292-9231.
<p>

<p>
<hr>
<center>
<a name="send"><h3>Send for Your Activism Guide Today</h3></a>[ <a href="#contents">Contents </a>]
</center>
<p>
If you have the dedication, we have the "how to" guide: <b>The Conservative Guide to Campus Activism</b>.  Published by Young America's Foundation, this guide is brimming with advice from successful former campus activists such as Congressman Dana Rohrabacher and Dinesh D'Souza. Chapters on hosting a speaker, fundraising, and getting local media coverage will assist students planning events for this spring and next fall. If you would like a free copy of the guide, call the Foundation today: 1-800-292-9231.
<p>

<p>
<hr>
<center>
<a name="meese"><h3> Meese Named Hermann Lecturer</h3></a>[ <a href="#contents">Contents </a>]
</center>
<p>
Young America's Foundation is proud to name the <b>Honorable Edwin Meese III </b>as the 1995 Grover Hermann Freedom Lecturer. Mr. Meese served under President Reagan as the 75th Attorney General of the United States. From 1981 to 1985, he was counselor to the president. In 1992, Mr. Meese wrote <b>With Reagan: The Inside Story</b>. As President Reagan's closest political confidante, Mr. Meese is uniquely qualified to reveal the true story of the Reagan presidency, free from the misconceptions perpetrated by critics. If you are interested in bringing Mr. Meese to your campus, please call <b>Michelle Sharp</b> at the Foundation: 1-800-292-9231.
<p>

<p>
<hr>
<center>
<a name="religious"><h3>Religious Students Under Fire on Campus</h3></a>[ <a href="#contents">Contents </a>]
</center>
<p>
Foundation Program Officer <b>Ron Rosenberger's</b> run-in with University of Virginia officials is a prime example of a disturbing trend: an alarming increase of flagrant discrimination against religious students and faculty members on campuses. In Ron's case, UVa denied his magazine, Wide Awake, funding, asserting that it was a religious activity advocating an "avowedly Christian" perspective. However, UVa had already funded the Muslim Students Association and Jewish Law Students Association. Young America's Foundation is currently conducting research on such discrimination. If you have experienced discrimination or intimidation first-hand, or are aware of examples on your campus, please call Ron Rosenberger at the Foundation: 1-800-292-9231.
<p>

<p>
<hr>
<center>
<a name="contact"><h3>Contact Information</h3></a>[ <a href="#contents">Contents </a>]
</center>
<p>
Campus Leader is published by Young America's Foundation.
<p>
Address all editorial matter, free subscription inquiries, and changes ot address to Campus Leader, 110 Elden Street, Herndon, Virginia 22070.
<p>
Young America's Foundation was formed in order to provide essential conferences, seminars, educational materials, scholarships and speakers to the young people ot America. As an educational organization, the Foundation strives to acquaint American youth with the principles of American government and the genius of the American political system in order that they may have a fuller understanding of contemporary public policy questions.<p>
<p>
