<head>
<title>Ron Robinson</title>
</head>

<body background="/yaf/ground2.gif">

<h2>Ron Robinson</h2>

<table align=left width="200" hspace="5">
<tr><td><img alt="Picture of Ron Robinson" src="ron.gif">
</td>
</tr>
</table>
<p>

	Ron Robinson is the president of Young America's Foundation. He received a Bachelors of Arts degree in political science at Canisius College and a Juris Doctor degree at The Catholic University of America. He is the publisher of Continuity and a contributor to The Conservative Guide to Campus Activism.<p>

	Mr. Robinson served as executive director of Young Americans for Freedom from 1977 through 1979, was president of the United States Youth Council from 1983 to 1985, and was president of the International Youth Year Commission in 1983 and 1984. He served as an advisor to the U.S. Department of Education during the Reagan Administration.<p>

	Mr. Robinson is a director of Citizens' United Foundation, a trustee of The Philadelphia Society, and the vice president of Free Speech Defense and Education Fund.<p>

	Mr. Robinson worked in the campaigns of Jack Kemp, James Buckley, Ronald Reagan, and Oliver North. He has appeared on a number of television programs including Firing Line, ABC's Person of the Week, and The Tom Snyder Show.<p>

	He is a member of the Virginia and U.S. Supreme Court Bars.<p><p>

