<h2>Kristen Kingsley</h2>

<table align=left width="200" hspace="5">
<tr><td><img alt="Picture of Kristen Kingsley" src="kristen.gif">
</td>
</tr>
</table><p>


<p>Kristen Kingsley is a program officer and the conference director for Young America's Foundation.  Kristen coordinates large regional leadership conferences throughout the country (including Atlanta, Richmond, and Los Angeles) as well as the week-long National Conservative Student Conference, held annually in Washington, D.C.  Kristen often speaks to student forums about conservative issues and was a recent guest on Newstalk TV, C-SPAN's Washington Journal.</p>
<p>Kristen joined the staff of Young America's Foundation in June of 1995, after graduating with honors from Wake Forest University with degrees in politics and speech communication.  During her college years, she was involved in numerous activites including Student Government Legislature, volunteer political campaign work, and Greek life.  She also served as the Student Chair of Freshman Orientation.</p>
<p>Kristen enjoys traveling and spent a semester in London, England where she interned at Entertainment Partnership, a public relations firm.  She interned with the Foundation in the summer of 1994.</p>
