<html>
<head>
<title>Matthew Schenk</title>
</head>

<body background="/yaf/ground2.gif">

<h2>Matthew Schenk</h2>

<table align=left width="200" hspace="5">
<tr><td><img alt="Picture of Matthew Schenk" src="matty.gif">
</td>
</tr>
</table>

        Matthew Schenk is a program officer for Young America's Foundation, and is the editor of Foundation publications <I>LIBERTAS</I> and <I>CAMPUS LEADER</I>.  He has represented the Foundation on several radio programs, including <I> The Armstrong Williams Show</I>, and has appeared several times on C-SPAN and on National Empowerment Television's <I>The Right Side</I>.<p> 
 
	Matthew received his B.A. from Swarthmore College in May of 1995, majoring in English Literature and minoring in Political Science.  As a sophomore, he served as Editor-in-Chief of the college newspaper, <I>The Phoenix</I>.  During his time at Swarthmore, Matthew also helped to establish the Swarthmore Conservative Union and the Swarthmore College Republicans.  To help Swarthmore students enjoy their Second Amendment rights, Matthew created a gun club at the college to foster gun appreciaton and education.  He also created and served as the editor of <I>Common Sense</I>, an independent and conservative journal of opinion.<p>
	
	Matthew, who joined the staff full-time in June of 1995, is also the Foundation's internet manager.  If you have any suggestions or questions about the Foundation's internet service, you should e-mail them to him at <a href="mailto:yaf@yaf.org">yaf@yaf.org</a><p><p>
<table align=right width="200" hspace="5">
<tr><td><img src="matliddy.gif" alt="matt, his wife, and Mr. and Mrs. G. Gordon Liddy"><BR>
Matthew and his wife Ronna (right) meet with Mr. and Mrs. G. Gordon Liddy at the Foundation's 1996 National Conservative Student Conference.
</td>
</tr>
</table>
<BR>
