<TITLE>Patrick X. Coyle</TITLE>
</HEAD>

<BODY background="/yaf/ground2.gif">

<h2>Patrick X. Coyle</h2>
<table align=left width="200" hspace="5">
<tr><td><img alt="Picture of Pat Coyle" src="patx.gif">
</td>
</tr>
</table>
<p>Patrick X. Coyle, Jr. is a Foundation Leadership Fellow, and is a recent graduate of Penn State University. Patrick first became active in politics by joining the Penn State Young Americans for Freedom (PS-YAF).  Patrick battled against the liberal orthodoxy during his years with PS-YAF.  He organized a protest against a liberal political science professor which gained nation-wide publicity, including a mention on the Rush Limbaugh Radio Program.  He also orchestrated a campus-wide petition drive against a proposed student activity fee.  Patrick worked with Young America's Foundation as a student to bring numerous speakers to his campus, such as Walter Williams, G. Gordon Liddy, and MTV's Kennedy.</P> 
<p>Patrick joined the Foundation as an intern in the summer of 1996.  He joined the staff full time in September 1996.</P>
