<p>Stephen Slivinski is an alumnus of Florida State University, where he received a B.S. in Economics and a B.S. in Literature.  Before he joined the Foundation in August as a Leadership Fellow, he was Director of the Institute for Conservative Studies at FSU; Research Associate at the James Madison Institute; Executive Producer and substitute host of "Florida On-Line," on WTAL, Florida's capital city's number one talk radio station; and Associate Editor of the <I>Independent Perspective</I>, FSU's premiere journal of conservative opinion.</p>
