<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE>The Heritage Foundation Internship Program  --  Program</TITLE>
<BODY BGCOLOR="F5F5F5">
<CENTER>
<FONT FACE="GENEVA" COLOR="RED"><H1>HERITAGE INTERNSHIP<BR>
PROGRAM</H1></FONT>
<BR>
<IMG SRC="learn.gif" WIDTH=291 HEIGHT=31 BORDER=0 ALT="Learn Today, Lead Tomorrow">
</CENTER>
<P>
<TABLE BORDER=0 ALIGN=LEFT CELLPADDING=5 CELLSPACING=5>
<TR>
<TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=CENTER WIDTH=120>

<P>
<A HREF="/heritage/intern_program/applictn.html"><IMG SRC="/heritage/intern_program/app.gif" WIDTH=108 HEIGHT=55 BORDER=0 ALT="Application button"></A>
<P>
<A HREF="/heritage/intern_program/program.html"><IMG SRC="/heritage/intern_program/pro.gif" WIDTH=108 HEIGHT=55 BORDER=0 ALT="Program button"></A>
<P>
<A HREF="/heritage/intern_program/resources.html"><IMG SRC="/heritage/intern_program/resource.gif" WIDTH=108 HEIGHT=55 BORDER=0 ALT="Resource button"></A>
<P>
<A HREF="/heritage/intern_program/projects.html"><IMG SRC="/heritage/intern_program/proj.gif" WIDTH=108 HEIGHT=55 BORDER=0 ALT="Projects button"></A>
<P>
<A HREF="/heritage/intern_program/96interns.gif"><IMG SRC="/heritage/intern_program/photo.gif" WIDTH=108 HEIGHT=55 BORDER=0 ALT="Picture button"></A>
<P>
<A HREF="/heritage/intern_program/alumni.html"><IMG SRC="/heritage/intern_program/alum.gif" WIDTH=108 HEIGHT=55 BORDER=0 ALT="Alumni button"></A>
</TD></TR></TABLE>

<TABLE BORDER=0 WIDTH=500 CELLPADDING=15 CELLSPACING=15>
<TR>
<TD VALIGN=TOP>
<CENTER>
<FONT FACE="GENEVA" COLOR="RED"><H3>
THE HERITAGE INTERN PROGRAM</H3></FONT>
</CENTER>
<P>
<DD>

Heritage offers interns ample opportunities to gain solid work experience.  As such, applications should reflect strong research and writing talents, excellent communication skills, and the inquisitiveness to undertake various research, writing, administrative, and computer projects.  In addition to their day-to-day assignments, interns attend weekly intern seminars designed to introduce them to the current policy debate and to conservative ideas.

<P>
<DD>
Interns are assigned to one of several departments within the Foundation depending on their interests, skills and availability.  For a listing and description of these departments, see our <A HREF="/heritage/intern_program/applicatn.html">internship application</A>. 

<P>
<B><U>Summer Internships:</U></B>  Each summer, The Heritage Foundation selects approximately fifty interns to work full-time for ten weeks in various departments.  This program offers a weekly salary of <B><U>$250.00</U></B>.

<P>
<B><U>Academic Year Internships:</U></B>  During the academic year, a smaller number of interns are chosen to work either part or full-time in various departments.  This program offers a stipend of <B><U>$8.00</U></B>    per diem to cover expenses.

<P>
<DD>
Heritage's program is comprised of four different components:  work experience, intern seminars, conservative reading group, and social and cultural activities.

<P>
<BLOCKQUOTE>
<CENTER><FONT FACE="GENEVA" COLOR="BLUE"><B>WORK EXPERIENCE</B></FONT>
</CENTER>

<P>

Interns gain solid experience conducting research for Heritage senior fellows, attending congressional briefings, and designing web-pages for Heritage's Internet site.  During his summer internship with <I>Policy Review</I>, Tyce Palmaffy wrote <A HREF="/heritage/p_review/sept96/labs.html">"Don't Brake for Big Government,"</A> for the magazine's Sept./October 1996 issue.

<P>
<CENTER><FONT FACE="GENEVA" COLOR="BLUE"><B>INTERN SEMINARS</B></FONT>
</CENTER>

<P>
Students hear from top policy experts at intern seminars.  Weekly seminars are conducted by congressional staffers, leading journalists, top Heritage domestic and foreign policy analysts, and Heritage Fellows such as former Attorney General Edwin Meese.  

<p>
<CENTER><FONT FACE="GENEVA" COLOR="BLUE"><B>CONSERVATIVE READING GROUP</B></FONT>
</CENTER>

<P>
Interns study the origins of conservative thought and the principles of American government in reading groups led by Educational Affairs staff.  Reading selections range from Aristotle and Machiavelli, to Washington and Jefferson, to Russell Kirk and Milton Friedman. 

<P>
<CENTER><FONT FACE="GENEVA" COLOR="BLUE"><B>
CULTURAL AND SOCIAL ACTIVITIES</B></FONT>
</CENTER>

<P>
Heritage's Intern Program sponsors cultural and social activities in Washington, D.C.  Past interns attended a taping of the McLaughlin Group, toured the White House and the Supreme Court, and, of course, played on Heritage's softball team, The Capitalist Tools. 

<P>
</BLOCKQUOTE>
</TD></TR></TABLE>

<CENTER>Return to the Heritage <A HREF="/heritage/intern_program/welcome.html">Intern Program page</A>
<P>

<A HREF="/heritage/hbut.map"><IMG SRC="/heritage/hbut.gif" width=540 length=67 ISMAP BORDER=0></A></CENTER>


</BODY>
