<TITLE>ANGELA M. ANTONELLI -- Heritage </TITLE>

<H3>ANGELA M. ANTONELLI</H3>
<B>Deputy Director, Roe Institute for Economic Policy Studies</B>
<P><IMG SRC="/heritage/staff/pics/antonel.jpe" ALIGN=LEFT HSPACE=10>

<P>
Antonelli comes to Heritage from Lewin-VHI Inc., a leading health-care econometrics firm in Fairfax, Va., where she assisted federal, state and private-sector clients in the design and implementation of proposals to reform the health-care system. Prior to working for Lewin-VHI, she was assistant branch chief in the White House's Office of Management and Budget with responsibilty for reviewing  regulations and information collection for the U.S. Departments of Labor, Treasury and Housing and Urban Development. She also briefed President Bush and Vice President Quayle's Council on Competitiveness on the domestic and international economic effects of new regulations.

A graduate of Cornell University, Antonelli earned her master's degree in public affairs from Princeton University. She succeeds Susan Eckerly who now works with Citizens for a Sound Economy. Antonelli lives in Washington, D.C.
