<title>Washington Watch: The Daily Radio Commentary</title>

<BODY bgcolor="#ffffff">

<center>

<a href="/townhall/FRC/images/topban.map">
<img src="/townhall/FRC/images/topban.gif" ismap border="0"></a>
<img src="/townhall/FRC/radio/gwatchbn.gif">

</center>

<p>

In this 90-second daily (Monday through Friday) radio commentary, former 
White House Domestic Policy Adviser Gary Bauer offers his insights on 
breaking (or about to break) news stories on family issues in the nation's 
capital.  This up-to-the-minute broadcast is a unique "window" on 
developments in the national public policy debate.  Bauer keeps a close 
eye on the White House, the Supreme Court, and the major media.  He takes 
the pulse of official Washington and reports stories you may not hear 
anywhere else, from the latest bureaucratic outrage to the sometimes 
startling data many pundits would rather you<I> not know</I>. Gary Bauer's 
daily commentary champions <B>truth in governing.</B>

<p>
<center><img src="/townhall/FRC/images/yllwline.gif"></center>
<p>

<center><h2>Broadcast Calendar</h2></center>

<p>

