<body bgcolor="#FFFFFF" background="/heritage/paperh.jpg">
<TITLE>WILLIAM W. BEACH -- Heritage </TITLE>

<H3>WILLIAM W. BEACH</H3>
<B>John M. Olin Senior Fellow in Economics</B>
<P><IMG SRC="/heritage/staff/pics/beach.jpe" ALIGN=LEFT HSPACE=10>
<P>
Beach will concentrate on tax and spending policy. His main emphasis will be to develop a computer model that estimates in detail the impact tax reform proposals such as the flat tax will have on families and businesses.  

Beach served as an economist for the state of Missouri from 1981-1985 where he designed and managed the state's econometric model and advised the governor on revenue and economic issues. Beach also has extensive experience in telecommunications, business development, marketing, economic analysis and non-profit fundraising.  

A graduate of Washburn University of Topeka, Kan., Beach earned a master's  degree in history and economics from the University of Missouri-Columbia. He lives in Fairfax, Va.

